summary: This document appears to be a technical specification or label for a Seagate hard drive (Model ST3120026AS, Serial 3JT1KOY7). It is marked as subject to a protective order and is part of the Epstein case document set, suggesting it is evidence or a seized item.
keyFacts: The document is a technical label for a Seagate 120GB hard drive (Model ST3120026AS, Serial 3JT1KOY7).
It is marked 'SUBJECT TO PROTECTIVE ORDER PARAGRAPHS 7, 8, 9, 10, 15, and 17', indicating it is evidence under court-ordered restrictions.
The document is part of the Epstein case files (EFTA00157462, referencing EFTA_00002286).
The drive was manufactured in Singapore for OEM distribution.
The label includes a caution that the product warranty is void if seals are removed or if the drive experiences shock over 350 Gs.
